caption: I love the bowls here and I’m not sure there’s many foods tastier than their fresh-made naan. Reasonably priced and filling.
I just love their food. I always get excellent service there. The place is well kept and the workers are always super friendly. Would recommend to others.
Love this place for a quick Indian flavored fast food meal

Quality, tasty and fresh food! Love Naan Stop. Employees are friendly and efficient and ok with last minute changes and helping with choosing items and sauces etc. The owners seem to be totally involved and they're very engaged and seem to really care about the food and their team members. I'd give more starts if I could! Everyone I know LOVES this small, local restaurant chain!
Excellent food, prompt service!

Order arrived late and cold to the touch. Tried contacting management with no response.  Edit: Blame their lack of quality control on "spam". Typical.

I had to call restaurant to make a change that I could not on the UE app for their 2 for 1 deal. They were great... polite and professional. The food was good, could be a little fresher. Packaging was sustainable and nothing dripped. The sauces and samosa I had was fantastic. However, the portion of veggie sides I got on my salad were very small. You expect for the lettuce to shrink, but sides should be healthy especially for a veggie meal. It's probably a better deal to buy pints for sides. Overall, tasty meal and I will likely order again.🙂

I've been to several Indian Fusion places across the nation and this place is at the top of my list. Amazing customer service and amazing food in a prime location. Just minutes away from attractions such as World of Coke etc. The owner and his family have a great recipes and a huge shout out to his mother who came up with them. Highly recommend the place!
I will be back with my friends. Prices are appropriate. I can see why they have so many great reviews.

This is by far the worst place to get Indian food.  I ordered chicken Marsala but it was gray and it was dry. It lacked the creaminess/ sauce and the fact my naan bread was burnt! I ordered 2 orders of Marsala and naan and they’re both a disappointment. It didn’t even taste like garlic but more like cardboard and the rice wasn’t even basmati and was sticky and clumpy. Let’s not forget the portion sizes are tiny as well. Would not recommend eating here I’d give the taste a 3/10
Updating my review. They have been super fast lately and the quality is great as always.

Tried this spot before with a friend and I am addicted ever since. I liked the awesome ambience and yummy food and drinks. I recommend this place.
Delicious vegetarian dish
Love this place. Paul was amazing! My ordered was delivered incorrectly and fixed it with no issue. Plus his people skills are popping!

Man this place is horrible I don’t know the lady name but we waited 40 minutes for our food Because she had to make more. Plus she kept forgetting my order then she gave us small portions of Our order talking about she need to have enough for other people. I said I order chicken masala I got three 3 cut up meats an rest is small not even a scoop of rice. Then she gave me one naan bread for three people to share. So now here we are waiting another 15 minutes for the rest of my order because she forgot the rest of the stuff.

This place is great to get a quick bite to eat. Everything is fresh and it's easy to eat healthy and still be satisfied by the delicious flavors. Gotta get the native Indian Hot chili cilantro chutney. The samosas are to die for and you can watch them make the naan right in front of you. This place is just as good as the NaanStop Downtown.

I ordered the palak paneer naanwich and it tasted horrible. The onions were bitter tasting and the worst thing was the naan was so burnt that it was flaking off. The fries were also overcooked and really hard.
Amazing food. My favs are the rice bowl and the samoosa!!! Neil and Kingsley are wonderful.  Highly recommend !

Located in a pretty convenient plaza. There are many options to choose from. Good Indian food and they constantly have promotion if you subscribed to the email list. Good place for fundraising as well if anybody is looking for a way to support their cause.
Not your traditional triangle shaped samosa but has the traditional samosa flavor. Reminds me of my childhood memories. I would definitely try out the other menu items when I get a chance.

I love this place! The food is consistent (shout out to the garlic naan and chicken tikka masala) and delicious, but the best part of Naan Stop is the staff. They’re always incredibly friendly and answer any questions you have. Also, a random side note is that the music is always super eclectic and fun. I never leave naan stop in a bad mood!
This the best naanstop, do not @ me saying otherwise. There is no yuppees around to decrease staff morale either. Never had bad order as opposed to the other two locations..
Nice place nice service nice food, good atmosphere
The Chicken Tikka and Samosa are pretty great for fast food Indian

Firstly, this is just a quick pick up spot if you’re in the mood for some Indian cuisine. However there were only 2 people working and as the only person in there it took 10 minutes for the guy to take our order. Then waited another 20 minutes for the naan to come out the oven and his reason was that the oven was cold. Advice for the owners, just hire 1 more person to work, it will help out a lot and you won’t lose customers that don’t want to wait on line for so long... at least 3 people walked out because of the wait. Food was good otherwise.

I am right in the middle with this place. I love the concept and the idea of fast food Indian BUT it was not executed well and the food lacked the flavor and kick that I am used to when I eat Indian.  My food fell short of being anything more pleasurable than eatable but it was eatable. My fries were creative in thought but was not executed well. I would have liked fresh fries instead of the generic frozen fries w/tikka masala and mint chutney, that both fell short individually. My wrap did not hold well... The Naan bread served as my base with Chicken Masala, corn and some sort of pickled slaw (which I thought was the star of this meal). Again, concept was great but you have to come correctly when we are talking Indian spiced food. Highlight of my meal would be the Organic Sodas, these were amazing!! I tried the Blood Orange and the LemonGrass. I would definitely look forward to these drinks. Unfortunately, if I returned, it would be to only drink the sodas. But I am optimistic that this idea can really work if the flavor profiles of the food improved.  It is worth a try. Just once though without improvement.

This place is my favored. I eat in plenty of restaurants but to this one I keep coming back again and again. The crew is very amicable and the cuisine they cook is so delicious. I never miss an opportunity to have a decent dinner in this place. Highly recommended.

Amazing food. It was my first trying it and the owner put up with my complications of not knowing what to get lol. The customer service was great, the owner was very nice and enthusiastic. Would definitely recommend this Indian food!!!

Came here yesterday at 11 am on 12/17. A tall, slender man wearing a black shirt served me. Too bad I didn’t catch his name because his service was great and he was friendly. I ordered brown rice bowl with paneer tikka and chola with medium and cool chutneys. Also, I ate a side order of naan. The food was fabulous. It seems like he tries hard to keep the restaurant clean, yet it is small and still seems a bit dirty in the kitchen. There was an unpleasant odor as if it is sour water. I don’t know where it’s coming from. The Naan Stop in Atlantic Station is nice and seems more clean, but the service quality was average (I’ve only been to that location once). Other than those things I would’ve given this place 5 stars.
While the rice bowl was good the hot chai was horrible in taste. If you are looking for hot tea with Indian taste then this is NOT the place to buy it. Definitely  not worth the money
If Chipotle made Indian food. It would be this.

I always say it’s like chipotle but Indian food instead. And it was so good! We got the double rice bowl, instead of two meals. And it was more than enough, especially because we made it a meal with a side and a drink (you get 15% if you’re a student). We got the tikka masala fries and oooooweee they were good. In the bowl we got the lentils and chickpeas as our protein, because you get to choose two. Then you add as many toppings as you want. And can add some sauces too. The workers were all so nice and cheery, added bonus. the location is kind of odd, we went on a Saturday at 330 and many businesses were already closed and the restaurant itself was not busy. So although weird, it was a cute street with string lights and very quiet.
The food tastes good.but the concept of rolling daal and Allo gobi in naan is not great as the naan becomes soggy real quick..
Parking is horrible but their service is pretty fast.
Not very authentically indian, but definitely some place to try out. Depends on your taste if you’d like it or not, but no harm in trying once. Kinda like fast-food.

I visited this place in expectation of good Indian food. I had Lamb, Rice and a Naan and I was super disappointed by the quality of food. Naan was very hard and difficult to chew. I returned back home with bad stomach☹️☹️

Great tasting and nice spot real relax

Terrible Experience - I placed a request for 2 hot chai - 1 for myself and 1 for my friend. We expected both chais to be served together because that is how a social beverage is enjoyed. Firstly, they served 1 hot chai 10 mins after placing the order (Since, freshly brewed tea takes that much time. So, I overlooked this delay.). But then they said that they are brewing the 2nd chai and that it will be ready in "5 minutes". (So, I wondered, that the 1st chai wasnt freshly made and still took 10 mins!) After 15 mins since the 1st chai was served we were still waiting for the 2nd chai. At this point, we requested that they refund the money, they again said 5 mins and conveniently turned their attention to the next customer. At that moment, we were so disappointed, frustrated, insulted that we decided to leave the place. Before leaving I asked my friend to have the one chai that we got and on the first sip, we knew that poor customer service was not the only thing this place was poor at, the chai tasted terrible. The entire content of the cup had to be discarded.  Basically, our time was wasted, our money was wasted (2 X $3.49) and we didnt get what we came for.  I have learned from this experience and I am not going there again.  On a not so important note, I am not a Indian food connoisseur but the taste of food here is like average. If you are hungry its okay but wouldnt recommend if you are looking for "authentic taste".

The service was very nice. They didn't try to sell me any other than what I asked for. The Tikka Marsala bowl was very middle of the road, the naan came about 5-7 minutes after I almost finished my meal. I really just wanted Tikka Marsala with naan, however that wasn't really an option. I won't be coming back.
Delicious
Food is great and the staff are awesome!

Naanstop used to be one of my favorite places for dinner downtown, but the quality has slipped severely over the past few months. Most recently, I ordered online but still had to wait for them to prepare the meal after the receipt said it would be "ready" and I showed up to pick it up. With a few hours left between when I ordered and closing, they seemed to be out of everything. Instead of offering to replace the now-impossible meal I had ordered with something comparable, the line chef tried to scrape together a rice bowl from the crusty scraps of rice at the bottom of the container and a few scant toppings. It barely looked like half of what the bowls used to look like. There seemed to be no plan to make any new ingredients, and maybe no staff to even do it in the first place! One of the kitchen-area cooks had tissues stuffed up his nose and kept wandering out into the dining area. I don't know if he had a nosebleed or a runny nose, but I'm sure he should not have been working that night. I really want to see this place get back to what it used to be and give it 5 stars, but based on the most recent experience and the last few visits before that, I cannot. Mixed up orders, slow staff, and just overall messiness compared to how it was before. It's a shame.

Local Indian fast fresh food! I already loved Indian food before trying this place, and the Mom's homemade recipes don't disappoint! If you're a novice to Indian food, have no worries. You control the spice level with the optional sauces. The garlic Naan sandwich is a great start. I don't eat chicken, so opt for the Turkey Kebab. You wouldn't even though it was turkey since it's well marinated in yogurt to produce a fluffy tender result. The rice bowls are just as good if you want to be less messy. I add the fresh spinach, cooked onions & peppers, and balance the heat with the Cool & Native sauces.  You will get head sweats!  Highly recommend the Mango Lassi drink to cool your mouth and balance your stomach. It's Mangos and yogurt whipped to delight with a little cinnamon and spice!
I like their naan. Order online you will have discount and coupons.

I have had lunch from NaanStop couple of times based upon that experience I decided to make a catering order for 22 people from them. They went above and beyond my experience. I was quite honestly a painful customer in the sense that I was indecisive in the process as I was not completely sure of what exactly I wanted! But they worked with me at every step of the way and made sure that everything went smoothly! The food was on time, the drop off and set up was very clean and with utensils! My only gripe is that the food smelled so good that we started digging in even before taking a picture. If one suggestion, I would recommend them to provide an even wider buffer option. Instead of 3 protiens maybe 4 protiens at an higher price point. Also please give an option to add masala fries in the future!  Thank you NaanStop

Since arriving in the downtown area, NaanStop has been consistently fantastic. The store is always clean, the food is always delicious, the staff is always friendly and attentive, and the owners are receptive and responsive to feedback. I most recently visited during their annual customer appreciation day (a practice no other Fairlie-Poplar eatery observes); the line extended out past the entrance and back to the corner. The customers were there to take advantage of the special offer (one-dollar entrees!), but the owners continuously worked the queue with lassi  samples, coupons for future visits (though the food alone is incentive enough), and frequent declarations of gratitude. Thanks to everyone involved in making my every NaanStop visit a superlative experience!
I didn't love India food until I had NaanStop
Amazing!
Food is 3/5 . Service is 5/5.
Great and lovely service !
Great food
Great food!!! Awesome concept and the staff are simply amazing!!!!!!!

I got the chicken tikka naanwhich and I have to be honest it tasted like I was eating a chili dog. My wife got a naanwhich with chick peas and it was okay, at best. The samosa were suprisingly decent though. The health rating was a 97/100 but the place and food bar looked disgusting. All I can say was the two female staff were very friendly and sweet. I definenlty would not eat here again even if it was free.
Grabbed a quick lunch.. I'm not one to usually choose vegetarian, but the chickpeas made for a tasty choice
Ordered the rice bowl and it was great. Hated the mango lassi. Ended up throwing it away. Gets crowded around noon.
Fast food Indian is a cool concept, I just didn't like the food that much
Everything is very bland, and is clearly a failed copy of a a "make your own meal" type of experience. This just leads to a boring experience of food and atmosphere
Too hot in the name of making it Indian.  The naan is not a naan but a thin "rumali roti".  However, the staff is friendly, helpful and happy :)  Mango lassi is cool
Good concept lousy food. The pander poorly made and OLD.  Forced tipping to check out.  Staff was pleasant
Food is so good! Nice staff, nice selection, very neat and organized space as well.
Desi Chipotle to be precise ...we should have more and more of these

i mean mango lassi, chai tea and cinnanaan! the masala fries are great too but i must watch my figure now. i choose the garlic naan when getting a sandwich. great fresh fast food. outdoor seating is available. some times, lunch hours and customer appreciation day, it gets crowded.
The best Indian food!
Not close to Indian food.
This place is awesome! It's like a cross between Chipotle and an Indian restaurant. Also, the samosas are great.

Stopped here for a quick bite while on the road. They sell quick service Indian food. The naan is baked fresh in a clay oven for each naanwich. I ate the lamb, my husband the chicken tikka masala and we shared samosas. I thought the lamb had a good flavor although it was slightly too sweet for my taste. The samosas were not as spicy as I prefer but good nonetheless. My husband really liked his sandwich. They have a spicy sauce you can get and he felt it was decently spicy. This is saying a lot considering he eats BWW blazin wings like they are candy. He loves spicy food and he never finds the food spicy enough. He enjoyed the spice level here. Said it was normal person extra spicy. So if you like a kick but don't want to burn off your taste buds it would be good for you. They have vegan and vegetarian options which includes fish.  Only issue I have with the place is the bathroom. The restaurant doesn't have its own bathroom. You have to walk down two flights of stairs and use the communal bathroom shared by several other restaurants and an apartment complex. The signage is poor and if my husband had not been with me I would have never found it. It is literally across a dining hall on the otherside of the building. It was clean though so I can't complain about that.  The staff was friendly and the facility was clean.  If we were in the area I would go back but would not make a special trip to frequent this establishment.  So if you are in the area, want a quick bite and like Indian food you should give it a try.
Delicious food! Great place to grab a bite if you're on campus later than usual. Not many places on broad open past 6, but I'm glad this one is!

Not authentic Indian, but delicious nonetheless. Cheap & quick as long as you avoid the main lunch rush. Pretty much like a Chipotle, in that you're picking a protein, some veggie add-ons, and sauces to put on top of a salad, rice, or naan base. Super friendly people behind the counter too!
TIR best good ever love it

So, so good. The customer service was excellent and the food was amazing. The hot sauce.... Whoa.... It was unbelievably delish. I especially wanted to leave a review because the people in front of us in line were especially picky and difficult, and the two girls who were helping them handled it with such impressive patience and grace that I wanted to make sure they got some credit. They helped each other out like a great team as well... Not leaving the other one under the bus. They also took pride in the quality of the food and preparation. There were 2 pieces of naan that ended up cooking a little too small for what their standard was so the other girl instantly stepped up and started making more while the other continued to help the guests. This helped keep the food quality standard what it should be while keeping efficiency. I was super impressed, and I've worked in the food industry for 16 years. Well done team naan stop!!

Easily the best Indian food I've had in a few years.  Brown rice bowl with chicken marsala, some slaw, the native Indian spicy chutney, garlic naan, and a drink came out to a little bit over $10. This place is definitely worth a visit whenever you are in the area.

WOW! So good. I will be back, and man the amount of food for the price is not bad either. I had the rice bowl with Chicken  Tikka Masala and the I spent a little more and got the Masala Fries. Everything was so good.

It used to be a 4-star place, but they've gotten pretty stingy. It's set up like Chipotle for Indian food, but it doesn't have Chipotle-like value. Sometimes it's easier to pay double and go here than wait at Rosa's next door.

Honestly the best Indian food. So authentic and delicious and great that you can customise the spice levels! And the staff are so friendly and helpful too. Would definitely recommend a visit! I've travelled in India and Naan Stop is the real deal!!
Really good, definitely going to be a regular place to eat for me.

I had experience of eating there several times. I have noted that they have reduced the amount of food they pour from past year up to know. Before for 7$ meal they gave you a full bowl of rice with full spoon size of chiken but try it now and see for yourself...Turmeric Bistro on peachtree mall charges you the same but it give you twice in quantity. The quality of noonstap is good but it is pricy.
Both veggie and non veg food is good here.
Awesome Indian food on the fly !

The first time I went, I got a rice bowl. The rice was undercooked and I was underwhelmed. I recently went back with a coworker who asked me to give it another try. I got a naanwich the second time and enjoyed it very much! It's not authentic Indian much like Chipotle isn't authentic Mexican, but it's fast, cheap, and delicious!
Good place. Casual, simple and affordable food. Friendly staff.
Great food at a reasonable price, the line moves very quickly.

Tried Paneer tikka masala with garlic naan and mango lassi. Paneer tikka and naan was good, while the mango lassi had some weird taste. The wrap quality was so bad that the inner layer (white color paper or something) came off when I took the gravy from wrap.
Good food, good folks.
I love the food specially rice with chicken masala and hot spices. But the people are impolite.
Fast hot Indian food!! Never would have thought!! In and out in less than. 5 mins with a great meal at a even better price!!!

This place is pretty good for a fast lunch. Like others have said, this isn't exactly authentic Indian fare, but more fast food Indian, what Chipotle is to Mexican food. You start with either a rice bowl or what they call a naanwhich, essentially the rice and whatever toppings you choose put in a naan and wrapped up like a burrito. I'd recommend the chicken tikka masala for the rice bowl/naanwhich. From there, add whatever toppings you'd like, again, much like you'd do at Chipotle. Figure you're going to spend roughly $7-8 on average.
Nice friendly .place great food
Great spot looooove the samosas
Great food, great quality??? Food is great during the day (lunch hour) good Indian-american food but after 6pm food is cold and hard(naan)  i would only go during the day time
Fast, Cheep, for Indian food. You only get two of three (Fast, Good, Cheap).
Love the lamb naanwhich
Very casual place on a cute street
It's basically Moe's for Indian food. Pretty good quality at good prices.
Very good ambiance. Food was a tad expensive but not more than chipotle. lots of food and very good for the price. Would recommend
I ordered the naanwich and it was a delight to my tastebuds!! I will be back!

This place opens at 10:30am. Today at 11:55 I walked in in a great mood, the young lady looked at me and started walking to the back. She then turned around and said, we're closed because rice is cooking for another ten minutes. I wasnt going to order rice so I asked, you're closed? I said your door is unlocked, sorry. She then repeated, we are closed till rice is done. Very rude.  Oddly last time I went they were also out of rice.  I uses to frequent this naanstop, today was my last time thanks to the rudeness of this young lady and being constantly out of food.
Shame to say it as Indian food. Please do not go to it if you are looking for a Lunch or dinner
The Samosa chat is spoiled and it smelled and tasted nasty!! never ever going back to this place. Just has a single spoon but made me sick..I'm thinking of reporting to the Health department.

Confused place, to begin with the prices on the board and menu card are different and the staff is clueless, they told us 'it's owners's problem, not my fault'  My wife took a menu suggested most popular combo and the staff again had no clue on how to bill it.  They were out of paneer curry so they added it from another curry, great! Ruined the taste of whole food.  What a useless and confused restaurant
Best samosas ever!!

I ordered the chicken tikka rice bowl with a samosa and a mango lassi. The service was a little slow but the staff was very friendly and prepared my samosa fresh. The food was very good and I look forward to coming back.

The first time I sampled this restaurants cuisine was at a food fair and it was awesome! It was my first introduction to Indian food and it left me wanting more! They consider themselves Indian fast food. You are able to get healthily bits here, and some Indian indulgent foods like a deep fried potato ball of goodness called Samosas! I had the lamb rapped in a Naanwhich and it was delicious! I totally recommend you check them out the food and customer service was wonderful!
Great fast food, a chipotle for Indian food!

THE BEST! I've tried other samosas in town, and none of them come close to the perfect golden, flavorful, taste that NaanStop has! My usual is the brown rice bowl with chicken tikka, peppers & onions, and ALL the chutneys :)

Not at all authentic Indian.  We were looking for a decent Indian restaurant in downtown near the attractions to take the parents visiting from India to.  Wanted them to feel more at home.  But the taste was far from authentic.  Perhaps we would have been better off going to a regular American restaurant.  At least we and the kids would have liked the food.  For parents, I would take them to places like Zyka or Madras Chettinad. For authentic Indian taste, I would not recommend this place at all.
Amazing, and quick, Indian food.  I love the Naanwiches.  Every sauce and filling I've tried has been delicious.
Incredible customer service!  I would go back again just because of the friendly staff, especially Gregory!
Imagine if chipotle served indian food. Bam. Naan stop. You can choose between a rice bowl or naan-wich and request all the fixings. Dont forget to grab one of their world famous Samosas!!

Great Indian food. I had an appointment down the road and I was running about an hour early. I walked into this store not really knowing what to expect. The best way I can describe it was that it was like a Moe's for Indian food. First you pick your meat, then your sauces and then the toppings. I had some chicken, with I don't know what is called but was a dark green sauce, some yogurt sauce, spinach leaves. WOW that was hot. Hotter than I could handle but it was so delicious I couldn't put it down. Next time I'm in the neighborhood I will try it with light green sauce, which isn't as hot. They also had some great vegetarian choices. If you go here be ready for some great food and with some loud jams going through the speakers.

Awesome food.  Nice location.  I'm not normally a fan of indian food, but this was really excellent and much different than the indian food I've had in the past.  I had the tandoori chicken naanwich with cool yogurt sauce and it was just superb.  Fresh, toasty bread and juicy meat.  I also had a samosa, which was like a sort of like a pastry with some spicier filling and cinnamony dip on the side (tasted good to my white-bread american taste buds) and made for a good dessert.  The guys behind the counter are friendly about describing what they had and recommending things, so don't be scared off by the unfamiliar menu...you'll be missing out!
Excellent all around! I recommend the samosa, chaat-style. YUMMY

Amazing food. Took a friend of mine from Delhi while he was in town for work and we both were impressed with the deliciousness factor here. I went for the Naanwich, he was eating paneer which I wanted to try but I knew I could count on the chicken. They let me go half and half no problem. I tried the hot chili chutney and the friendly sandwichista recommended the yogurt sauce to round it out. Tried the fries, very good, and the samosa?s were so so. Oh, the naanstop beverage was quite thick yet delicious.
